08/08/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Office of the High Representative (OHR) has voiced support for BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic's recent proposal that BiH and Serbia-Montenegro launch a joint police team, focused on apprehending war crimes indictees. 
On Friday (6 August), the Sarajevo-based news agency Fena quoted OHR spokesman Oleg Milisic as saying the initiative was "welcome and necessary". 
(Fena - 06/08/04)
